    {
      "id": "5a93c517_c734764c",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/policy/charts/drools/values.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 33,
      "message": "I guess I am not sure.   Probably what you have is good.  Let me try to explain my concern a bit better and you tell me if it is addressed in the review.\n\nWhat we need is similar to what we talked about for the PDP component.   The PDP component should be statically scalable, so I think we agreed on 3 PDPs active within a cluster (the service).\n\nFor PDP-D, drools pdp, we need exactly the same but instead of 3 (which I am not sure that's the value that we agreed at the end).   It should be 4, so 4 active PDP-Ds (drools components) part of the service.\n\nSimilarly to the agreements we had for the pdp component.   We should have 4 distinct addresses known a priori for each pdp-d component (drools component), so they can be addressed individually at well known locations if needed.\n\nDoes it make sense what I am asking for?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 477,
        "name": "Jorge Hernandez",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jorge.hernandez-herrero@att.com",
        "username": "jhh"
      },
      "updated": "2018-03-23 12:37:22.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "5a93c517_a1691a27",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "5a93c517_876c2e38",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/policy/charts/drools/charts/nexus/templates/deployment.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 65,
      "message": "We also need a persistent volume of this directory for nexus component to survive failures.   \n\nThe volume is set internally in the docker image with\n\nVOLUME /opt/nexus/sonatype-work\n\nCan it be added for the nexus component?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 477,
        "name": "Jorge Hernandez",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jorge.hernandez-herrero@att.com",
        "username": "jhh"
      },
      "updated": "2018-03-23 12:44:45.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
